
Overview of verb saddle

The verb saddle has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) saddle -- (put a saddle on; "saddle the horses")
2. (1) saddle -- (load or burden; encumber; "he saddled me with that heavy responsibility")
3. (1) charge, saddle, burden -- (impose a task upon, assign a responsibility to; "He charged her with cleaning up all the files over the weekend")

Overview of adj saddled

The adj saddled has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. saddled -- (having a saddle on or being mounted on a saddled animal; "saddled and spurred and ready to ride")
2. saddled -- (subject to an imposed burden; "left me saddled with the bill"; "found himself saddled with more responsibility than power")
